{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"If you really want to understand"},{"time":3000,"text":"the problem that we're facing with the oceans,"},{"time":6000,"text":"you have to think about the biology"},{"time":8000,"text":"at the same time you think about the physics."},{"time":11000,"text":"We can't solve the problems"},{"time":13000,"text":"unless we start studying the ocean"},{"time":15000,"text":"in a very much more interdisciplinary way."},{"time":18000,"text":"So I'm going to demonstrate that through"},{"time":20000,"text":"discussion of some of the climate change things that are going on in the ocean."},{"time":23000,"text":"We'll look at sea level rise."},{"time":25000,"text":"We'll look at ocean warming."},{"time":27000,"text":"And then the last thing on the list there, ocean acidification --"},{"time":30000,"text":"if you were to ask me, you know, \"What do you worry about the most?"},{"time":33000,"text":"What frightens you?\""},{"time":35000,"text":"for me, it's ocean acidification."},{"time":37000,"text":"And this has come onto the stage pretty recently."},{"time":39000,"text":"So I will spend a little time at the end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"I was in Copenhagen in December"},{"time":44000,"text":"like a number of you in this room."},{"time":46000,"text":"And I think we all found it, simultaneously,"},{"time":49000,"text":"an eye-opening"},{"time":51000,"text":"and a very frustrating experience."},{"time":53000,"text":"I sat in this large negotiation hall,"},{"time":56000,"text":"at one point, for three or four hours,"},{"time":58000,"text":"without hearing the word \"oceans\" one time."},{"time":62000,"text":"It really wasn't on the radar screen."},{"time":65000,"text":"The nations that brought it up"},{"time":67000,"text":"when we had the speeches of the national leaders --"},{"time":69000,"text":"it tended to be the leaders of the small island states,"},{"time":72000,"text":"the low-lying island states."},{"time":74000,"text":"And by this weird quirk"},{"time":76000,"text":"of alphabetical order of the nations,"},{"time":79000,"text":"a lot of the low-lying states,"},{"time":81000,"text":"like Kiribati and Nauru,"},{"time":83000,"text":"they were seated at the very end of these immensely long rows."},{"time":86000,"text":"You know, they were marginalized"},{"time":88000,"text":"in the negotiation room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"One of the problems"},{"time":92000,"text":"is coming up with the right target."},{"time":94000,"text":"It's not clear what the target should be."},{"time":96000,"text":"And how can you figure out how to fix something"},{"time":98000,"text":"if you don't have a clear target?"},{"time":100000,"text":"Now, you've heard about \"two degrees\":"},{"time":102000,"text":"that we should limit temperature rise to no more than two degrees."},{"time":105000,"text":"But there's not a lot of science behind that number."},{"time":108000,"text":"We've also talked about"},{"time":110000,"text":"concentrations of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere."},{"time":112000,"text":"Should it be 450? Should it be 400?"},{"time":115000,"text":"There's not a lot of science behind that one either."},{"time":118000,"text":"Most of the science that is behind these numbers,"},{"time":120000,"text":"these potential targets,"},{"time":122000,"text":"is based on studies on land."},{"time":124000,"text":"And I would say, for the people that work in the ocean"},{"time":127000,"text":"and think about what the targets should be,"},{"time":129000,"text":"we would argue that they must be much lower."},{"time":131000,"text":"You know, from an oceanic perspective,"},{"time":133000,"text":"450 is way too high."},{"time":135000,"text":"Now there's compelling evidence"},{"time":137000,"text":"that it really needs to be 350."},{"time":139000,"text":"We are, right now, at 390 parts per million"},{"time":142000,"text":"of CO2 in the atmosphere."},{"time":144000,"text":"We're not going to put the brakes on in time to stop at 450,"},{"time":147000,"text":"so we've got to accept we're going to do an overshoot,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and the discussion as we go forward"},{"time":152000,"text":"has to focus on how far the overshoot goes"},{"time":155000,"text":"and what's the pathway back to 350."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158000,"text":"Now, why is this so complicated?"},{"time":160000,"text":"Why don't we know some of these things a little bit better?"},{"time":162000,"text":"Well, the problem is that"},{"time":164000,"text":"we've got very complicated forces in the climate system."},{"time":166000,"text":"There's all kinds of natural causes of climate change."},{"time":169000,"text":"There's air-sea interactions."},{"time":171000,"text":"Here in Galapagos,"},{"time":173000,"text":"we're affected by El Ninos and La Nina."},{"time":175000,"text":"But the entire planet warms up when there's a big El Nino."},{"time":178000,"text":"Volcanoes eject aerosols into the atmosphere."},{"time":181000,"text":"That changes our climate."},{"time":183000,"text":"The ocean contains most of the exchangeable heat on the planet."},{"time":186000,"text":"So anything that influences"},{"time":188000,"text":"how ocean surface waters mix with the deep water"},{"time":191000,"text":"changes the ocean of the planet."},{"time":193000,"text":"And we know the solar output's not constant through time."},{"time":196000,"text":"So those are all natural causes of climate change."},{"time":199000,"text":"And then we have the human-induced causes"},{"time":201000,"text":"of climate change as well."},{"time":203000,"text":"We're changing the characteristics of the surface of the land,"},{"time":205000,"text":"the reflectivity."},{"time":207000,"text":"We inject our own aerosols into the atmosphere,"},{"time":209000,"text":"and we have trace gases, and not just carbon dioxide --"},{"time":212000,"text":"it's methane, ozone,"},{"time":214000,"text":"oxides of sulfur and nitrogen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"So here's the thing. It sounds like a simple question."},{"time":218000,"text":"Is CO2 produced by man's activities"},{"time":221000,"text":"causing the planet to warm up?"},{"time":223000,"text":"But to answer that question,"},{"time":225000,"text":"to make a clear attribution to carbon dioxide,"},{"time":228000,"text":"you have to know something about"},{"time":230000,"text":"all of these other agents of change."},{"time":232000,"text":"But the fact is we do know a lot about all of those things."},{"time":235000,"text":"You know, thousands of scientists"},{"time":237000,"text":"have been working on understanding"},{"time":239000,"text":"all of these man-made causes"},{"time":241000,"text":"and the natural causes."},{"time":243000,"text":"And we've got it worked out, and we can say,"},{"time":246000,"text":"\"Yes, CO2 is causing the planet to warm up now.\""},{"time":250000,"text":"Now, we have many ways to study natural variability."},{"time":253000,"text":"I'll show you a few examples of this now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"This is the ship that I spent the last three months on in the Antarctic."},{"time":258000,"text":"It's a scientific drilling vessel."},{"time":261000,"text":"We go out for months at a time and drill into the sea bed"},{"time":264000,"text":"to recover sediments"},{"time":266000,"text":"that tell us stories of climate change, right."},{"time":269000,"text":"Like one of the ways to understand our greenhouse future"},{"time":272000,"text":"is to drill down in time"},{"time":274000,"text":"to the last period"},{"time":276000,"text":"where we had CO2 double what it is today."},{"time":278000,"text":"And so that's what we've done with this ship."},{"time":280000,"text":"This was -- this is south of the Antarctic Circle."},{"time":283000,"text":"It looks downright tropical there."},{"time":285000,"text":"One day where we had calm seas and sun,"},{"time":288000,"text":"which was the reason I could get off the ship."},{"time":290000,"text":"Most of the time it looked like this."},{"time":292000,"text":"We had a waves up to 50 ft."},{"time":295000,"text":"and winds averaging"},{"time":297000,"text":"about 40 knots for most of the voyage"},{"time":299000,"text":"and up to 70 or 80 knots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"So that trip just ended,"},{"time":303000,"text":"and I can't show you too many results from that right now,"},{"time":305000,"text":"but we'll go back one more year,"},{"time":307000,"text":"to another drilling expedition I've been involved in."},{"time":310000,"text":"This was led by Ross Powell and Tim Naish."},{"time":313000,"text":"It's the ANDRILL project."},{"time":315000,"text":"And we made the very first bore hole"},{"time":317000,"text":"through the largest floating ice shelf on the planet."},{"time":319000,"text":"This is a crazy thing, this big drill rig wrapped in a blanket"},{"time":322000,"text":"to keep everybody warm,"},{"time":324000,"text":"drilling at temperatures of minus 40."},{"time":326000,"text":"And we drilled in the Ross Sea."},{"time":328000,"text":"That's the Ross Sea Ice Shelf on the right there."},{"time":331000,"text":"So, this huge floating ice shelf"},{"time":333000,"text":"the size of Alaska"},{"time":335000,"text":"comes from West Antarctica."},{"time":337000,"text":"Now, West Antarctica is the part of the continent"},{"time":340000,"text":"where the ice is grounded on sea floor"},{"time":342000,"text":"as much as 2,000 meters deep."},{"time":345000,"text":"So that ice sheet is partly floating,"},{"time":347000,"text":"and it's exposed to the ocean, to the ocean heat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"This is the part of Antarctica that we worry about."},{"time":353000,"text":"Because it's partly floating, you can imagine,"},{"time":355000,"text":"is sea level rises a little bit,"},{"time":357000,"text":"the ice lifts off the bed, and then it can break off and float north."},{"time":360000,"text":"When that ice melts, sea level rises by six meters."},{"time":364000,"text":"So we drill back in time to see how often that's happened,"},{"time":367000,"text":"and exactly how fast that ice can melt."},{"time":370000,"text":"Here's the cartoon on the left there."},{"time":373000,"text":"We drilled through a hundred meters of floating ice shelf"},{"time":376000,"text":"then through 900 meters of water"},{"time":378000,"text":"and then 1,300 meters into the sea floor."},{"time":381000,"text":"So it's the deepest geological bore hole ever drilled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"It took about 10 years to put this project together."},{"time":387000,"text":"And here's what we found."},{"time":389000,"text":"Now, there's 40 scientists working on this project,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and people are doing all kinds of really complicated"},{"time":393000,"text":"and expensive analyses."},{"time":396000,"text":"But it turns out, you know, the thing that told the best story"},{"time":399000,"text":"was this simple visual description."},{"time":401000,"text":"You know, we saw this in the core samples as they came up."},{"time":404000,"text":"We saw these alternations"},{"time":406000,"text":"between sediments that look like this --"},{"time":408000,"text":"there's gravel and cobbles in there"},{"time":410000,"text":"and a bunch of sand."},{"time":412000,"text":"That's the kind of material in the deep sea."},{"time":414000,"text":"It can only get there if it's carried out by ice."},{"time":417000,"text":"So we know there's an ice shelf overhead."},{"time":419000,"text":"And that alternates with a sediment that looks like this."},{"time":422000,"text":"This is absolutely beautiful stuff."},{"time":424000,"text":"This sediment is 100 percent made up"},{"time":426000,"text":"of the shells of microscopic plants."},{"time":429000,"text":"And these plants need sunlight,"},{"time":431000,"text":"so we know when we find that sediment"},{"time":433000,"text":"there's no ice overhead."},{"time":435000,"text":"And we saw about 35 alternations"},{"time":437000,"text":"between open water and ice-covered water,"},{"time":440000,"text":"between gravels and these plant sediments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"So what that means is, what it tells us"},{"time":446000,"text":"is that the Ross Sea region, this ice shelf,"},{"time":449000,"text":"melted back and formed anew"},{"time":451000,"text":"about 35 times."},{"time":453000,"text":"And this is in the past four million years."},{"time":457000,"text":"This was completely unexpected."},{"time":459000,"text":"Nobody imagined that the West Antarctic Ice Sheet"},{"time":461000,"text":"was this dynamic."},{"time":463000,"text":"In fact, the lore for many years has been,"},{"time":466000,"text":"\"The ice formed many tens of millions of years ago,"},{"time":468000,"text":"and it's been there ever since.\""},{"time":470000,"text":"And now we know that in our recent past"},{"time":472000,"text":"it melted back and formed again,"},{"time":474000,"text":"and sea level went up and down, six meters at a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477000,"text":"What caused it?"},{"time":479000,"text":"Well, we're pretty sure that it's very small changes"},{"time":481000,"text":"in the amount of sunlight reaching Antarctica,"},{"time":484000,"text":"just caused by natural changes in the orbit of the Earth."},{"time":487000,"text":"But here's the key thing:"},{"time":489000,"text":"you know, the other thing we found out"},{"time":491000,"text":"is that the ice sheet passed a threshold,"},{"time":493000,"text":"that the planet warmed up enough --"},{"time":495000,"text":"and the number's about one degree to one and a half degrees Centigrade --"},{"time":497000,"text":"the planet warmed up enough that it became ..."},{"time":500000,"text":"that ice sheet became very dynamic"},{"time":502000,"text":"and was very easily melted."},{"time":504000,"text":"And you know what?"},{"time":506000,"text":"We've actually changed the temperature in the last century"},{"time":508000,"text":"just the right amount."},{"time":510000,"text":"So many of us are convinced now"},{"time":513000,"text":"that West Antarctica, the West Antarctic Ice Sheet, is starting to melt."},{"time":516000,"text":"We do expect to see a sea-level rise"},{"time":519000,"text":"on the order of one to two meters by the end of this century."},{"time":522000,"text":"And it could be larger than that."},{"time":525000,"text":"This is a serious consequence"},{"time":527000,"text":"for nations like Kiribati,"},{"time":529000,"text":"you know, where the average elevation"},{"time":531000,"text":"is about a little over a meter above sea level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"Okay, the second story takes place here in Galapagos."},{"time":536000,"text":"This is a bleached coral,"},{"time":538000,"text":"coral that died during the 1982-'83 El Nino."},{"time":541000,"text":"This is from Champion Island."},{"time":543000,"text":"It's about a meter tall Pavona clavus colony."},{"time":546000,"text":"And it's covered with algae. That's what happens."},{"time":549000,"text":"When these things die,"},{"time":551000,"text":"immediately, organisms come in"},{"time":553000,"text":"and encrust and live on that dead surface."},{"time":556000,"text":"And so, when a coral colony is killed"},{"time":558000,"text":"by an El Nino event,"},{"time":560000,"text":"it leaves this indelible record."},{"time":562000,"text":"You can go then and study corals"},{"time":564000,"text":"and figure out how often do you see this."},{"time":566000,"text":"So one of the things thought of in the '80s"},{"time":568000,"text":"was to go back and take cores"},{"time":570000,"text":"of coral heads throughout the Galapagos"},{"time":572000,"text":"and find out how often was there a devastating event."},{"time":575000,"text":"And just so you know, 1982-'83,"},{"time":578000,"text":"that El Nino killed 95 percent"},{"time":580000,"text":"of all the corals here in Galapagos."},{"time":583000,"text":"Then there was similar mortality in '97-'98."},{"time":586000,"text":"And what we found"},{"time":588000,"text":"after drilling back in time two to 400 years"},{"time":590000,"text":"was that these were unique events."},{"time":592000,"text":"We saw no other mass mortality events."},{"time":595000,"text":"So these events in our recent past really are unique."},{"time":598000,"text":"So they're either just truly monster El Ninos,"},{"time":600000,"text":"or they're just very strong El Ninos"},{"time":602000,"text":"that occurred against a backdrop of global warming."},{"time":606000,"text":"Either case, it's bad news"},{"time":608000,"text":"for the corals of the Galapagos Islands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612000,"text":"Here's how we sample the corals."},{"time":614000,"text":"This is actually Easter Island. Look at this monster."},{"time":617000,"text":"This coral is eight meters tall, right."},{"time":620000,"text":"And it been growing for about 600 years."},{"time":622000,"text":"Now, Sylvia Earle turned me on to this exact same coral."},{"time":625000,"text":"And she was diving here with John Lauret -- I think it was 1994 --"},{"time":628000,"text":"and collected a little nugget and sent it to me."},{"time":630000,"text":"And we started working on it,"},{"time":632000,"text":"and we figured out we could tell the temperature of the ancient ocean"},{"time":634000,"text":"from analyzing a coral like this."},{"time":637000,"text":"So we have a diamond drill."},{"time":639000,"text":"We're not killing the colony; we're taking a small core sample out of the top."},{"time":642000,"text":"The core comes up as these cylindrical tubes of limestone."},{"time":645000,"text":"And that material then we take back to the lab and analyze it."},{"time":649000,"text":"You can see some of the coral cores there on the right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652000,"text":"So we've done that all over the Eastern Pacific."},{"time":654000,"text":"We're starting to do it in the Western Pacific as well."},{"time":657000,"text":"I'll take you back here to the Galapagos Islands."},{"time":659000,"text":"And we've been working at this fascinating uplift here in Urbina Bay."},{"time":662000,"text":"That the place where,"},{"time":664000,"text":"during an earthquake in 1954,"},{"time":666000,"text":"this marine terrace was lifted up"},{"time":668000,"text":"out of the ocean very quickly,"},{"time":671000,"text":"and it was lifted up about six to seven meters."},{"time":674000,"text":"And so now you can walk through a coral reef without getting wet."},{"time":677000,"text":"If you go on the ground there, it looks like this,"},{"time":679000,"text":"and this is the grandaddy coral."},{"time":681000,"text":"It's 11 meters in diameter,"},{"time":683000,"text":"and we know that it started growing"},{"time":685000,"text":"in the year 1584."},{"time":687000,"text":"Imagine that."},{"time":689000,"text":"And that coral was growing happily in those shallow waters,"},{"time":692000,"text":"until 1954, when the earthquake happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"Now the reason we know it's 1584"},{"time":697000,"text":"is that these corals have growth bands."},{"time":699000,"text":"When you cut them, slice those cores in half and x-ray them,"},{"time":702000,"text":"you see these light and dark bands."},{"time":704000,"text":"Each one of those is a year."},{"time":706000,"text":"We know these corals grow about a centimeter and a half a year."},{"time":708000,"text":"And we just count on down to the bottom."},{"time":711000,"text":"Then their other attribute is"},{"time":713000,"text":"that they have this great chemistry."},{"time":715000,"text":"We can analyze the carbonate"},{"time":717000,"text":"that makes up the coral,"},{"time":719000,"text":"and there's a whole bunch of things we can do."},{"time":721000,"text":"But in this case, we measured the different isotopes of oxygen."},{"time":724000,"text":"Their ratio tells us the water temperature."},{"time":726000,"text":"In this example here,"},{"time":728000,"text":"we had monitored this reef in Galapagos"},{"time":730000,"text":"with temperature recorders,"},{"time":732000,"text":"so we know the temperature of the water the coral's growing in."},{"time":735000,"text":"Then after we harvest a coral, we measure this ratio,"},{"time":738000,"text":"and now you can see, those curves match perfectly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741000,"text":"In this case, at these islands,"},{"time":743000,"text":"you know, corals"},{"time":745000,"text":"are instrumental-quality recorders of change in the water."},{"time":748000,"text":"And of course, our thermometers"},{"time":750000,"text":"only take us back 50 years or so here."},{"time":752000,"text":"The coral can take us back"},{"time":754000,"text":"hundreds and thousands of years."},{"time":756000,"text":"So, what we do:"},{"time":758000,"text":"we've merged a lot of different data sets."},{"time":761000,"text":"It's not just my group; there's maybe 30 groups worldwide doing this."},{"time":764000,"text":"But we get these instrumental- and near-instrumental-quality records"},{"time":767000,"text":"of temperature change that go back hundreds of years,"},{"time":769000,"text":"and we put them together."},{"time":771000,"text":"Here's a synthetic diagram."},{"time":773000,"text":"There's a whole family of curves here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"But what's happening: we're looking at the last thousand years"},{"time":778000,"text":"of temperature on the planet."},{"time":780000,"text":"And there's five or six different compilations there,"},{"time":782000,"text":"But each one of those compilations reflects input"},{"time":785000,"text":"from hundreds of these kinds of records from corals."},{"time":788000,"text":"We do similar things with ice cores."},{"time":791000,"text":"We work with tree rings."},{"time":793000,"text":"And that's how we discover"},{"time":795000,"text":"what is truly natural"},{"time":797000,"text":"and how different is the last century, right?"},{"time":800000,"text":"And I chose this one"},{"time":802000,"text":"because it's complicated and messy looking, right."},{"time":805000,"text":"This is as messy as it gets."},{"time":807000,"text":"You can see there's some signals there."},{"time":810000,"text":"Some of the records"},{"time":812000,"text":"show lower temperatures than others."},{"time":814000,"text":"Some of them show greater variability."},{"time":817000,"text":"But they all tell us"},{"time":819000,"text":"what the natural variability is."},{"time":821000,"text":"Some of them are from the northern hemisphere;"},{"time":823000,"text":"some are from the entire globe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"But here's what we can say:"},{"time":827000,"text":"what's natural in the last thousand years is that the planet was cooling down."},{"time":830000,"text":"It was cooling down"},{"time":832000,"text":"until about 1900 or so."},{"time":834000,"text":"And there is natural variability"},{"time":836000,"text":"caused by the Sun, caused by El Ninos."},{"time":839000,"text":"A century-scale, decadal-scale variability,"},{"time":841000,"text":"and we know the magnitude;"},{"time":843000,"text":"it's about two-tenths to four-tenths of a degree Centigrade."},{"time":846000,"text":"But then at the very end is where"},{"time":848000,"text":"we have the instrumental record in black."},{"time":850000,"text":"And there's the temperature up there in 2009."},{"time":853000,"text":"You know, we've warmed the globe"},{"time":855000,"text":"about a degree Centigrade in the last century,"},{"time":858000,"text":"and there's nothing"},{"time":860000,"text":"in the natural part of that record"},{"time":862000,"text":"that resembles what we've seen in the last century."},{"time":864000,"text":"You know, that's the strength of our argument,"},{"time":866000,"text":"that we are doing something that's truly different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870000,"text":"So I'll close with a short discussion"},{"time":873000,"text":"of ocean acidification."},{"time":876000,"text":"I like it as a component of global change to talk about,"},{"time":879000,"text":"because, even if you are a hard-bitten global warming skeptic,"},{"time":883000,"text":"and I talk to that community fairly often,"},{"time":885000,"text":"you cannot deny"},{"time":887000,"text":"the simple physics"},{"time":889000,"text":"of CO2 dissolving in the ocean."},{"time":892000,"text":"You know, we're pumping out lots of CO2 into the atmosphere,"},{"time":895000,"text":"from fossil fuels, from cement production."},{"time":898000,"text":"Right now, about a third of that carbon dioxide"},{"time":900000,"text":"is dissolving straight into the sea, right?"},{"time":902000,"text":"And as it does so,"},{"time":904000,"text":"it makes the ocean more acidic."},{"time":907000,"text":"So, you cannot argue with that."},{"time":909000,"text":"That is what's happening right now,"},{"time":911000,"text":"and it's a very different issue"},{"time":913000,"text":"than the global warming issue."},{"time":915000,"text":"It has many consequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917000,"text":"There's consequences for carbonate organisms."},{"time":920000,"text":"There are many organisms"},{"time":922000,"text":"that build their shells out of calcium carbonate --"},{"time":924000,"text":"plants and animals both."},{"time":927000,"text":"The main framework material of coral reefs"},{"time":929000,"text":"is calcium carbonate."},{"time":931000,"text":"That material is more soluble"},{"time":933000,"text":"in acidic fluid."},{"time":936000,"text":"So one of the things we're seeing"},{"time":938000,"text":"is organisms are having"},{"time":940000,"text":"to spend more metabolic energy"},{"time":942000,"text":"to build and maintain their shells."},{"time":944000,"text":"At some point, as this transience,"},{"time":946000,"text":"as this CO2 uptake in the ocean continues,"},{"time":949000,"text":"that material's actually going to start to dissolve."},{"time":951000,"text":"And on coral reefs,"},{"time":953000,"text":"where some of the main framework organisms disappear,"},{"time":956000,"text":"we will see a major loss"},{"time":958000,"text":"of marine biodiversity."},{"time":960000,"text":"But it's not just the carbonate producers that are affected."},{"time":963000,"text":"There's many physiological processes"},{"time":966000,"text":"that are influenced by the acidity of the ocean."},{"time":969000,"text":"So many reactions involving enzymes and proteins"},{"time":972000,"text":"are sensitive to the acid content of the ocean."},{"time":975000,"text":"So, all of these things --"},{"time":977000,"text":"greater metabolic demands,"},{"time":979000,"text":"reduced reproductive success,"},{"time":981000,"text":"changes in respiration and metabolism."},{"time":984000,"text":"You know, these are things that we have good physiological reasons"},{"time":987000,"text":"to expect to see stressed"},{"time":989000,"text":"caused by this transience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991000,"text":"So we figured out some pretty interesting ways"},{"time":993000,"text":"to track CO2 levels in the atmosphere,"},{"time":996000,"text":"going back millions of years."},{"time":998000,"text":"We used to do it just with ice cores,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"but in this case, we're going back 20 million years."},{"time":1003000,"text":"And we take samples of the sediment,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"and it tells us the CO2 level of the ocean,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"and therefore the CO2 level of the atmosphere."},{"time":1010000,"text":"And here's the thing:"},{"time":1012000,"text":"you have to go back about 15 million years"},{"time":1014000,"text":"to find a time when CO2 levels"},{"time":1017000,"text":"were about what they are today."},{"time":1019000,"text":"You have to go back about 30 million years"},{"time":1021000,"text":"to find a time when CO2 levels"},{"time":1023000,"text":"were double what they are today."},{"time":1025000,"text":"Now, what that means is"},{"time":1027000,"text":"that all of the organisms that live in the sea"},{"time":1029000,"text":"have evolved in this chemostatted ocean,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"with CO2 levels lower than they are today."},{"time":1035000,"text":"That's the reason that they're not able to respond or adapt"},{"time":1038000,"text":"to this rapid acidification"},{"time":1041000,"text":"that's going on right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043000,"text":"So, Charlie Veron"},{"time":1045000,"text":"came up with this statement last year:"},{"time":1047000,"text":"\"The prospect of ocean acidification"},{"time":1049000,"text":"may well be the most serious"},{"time":1051000,"text":"of all of the predicted outcomes"},{"time":1053000,"text":"of anthropogenic CO2 release.\""},{"time":1056000,"text":"And I think that may very well be true,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"so I'll close with this."},{"time":1061000,"text":"You know, we do need the protected areas, absolutely,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"but for the sake of the oceans,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"we have to cap or limit CO2 emissions"},{"time":1068000,"text":"as soon as possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}